{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0121RcVSrLUZpNrmrUz8M2Ny","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The bug is clear. The removed line is `best_atom.length = atom.length;` at line 1074 (before the deletion). When a better quality atom is found (quality > best_quality), the code copies the bytes and mask from `atom` to `best_atom`, but without the deleted line, it never updates `best_atom.length` to match `atom.length`. \n\nThis means `best_atom.length` retains its old value (from the previous best atom), causing `best_atom` to have an inconsistent length field — either truncating the valid bytes or claiming more bytes than were actually set.\n\n**ROOT CAUSE:** `libyara/atoms.c:1074` (after the deletion, now the missing line was between the loop and `best_quality = quality;`). In `_yr_atoms_extract_from_re`, when a sliding window of RE nodes yields a higher-quality atom, the bytes and mask arrays of `best_atom` are updated but `best_atom.length` is never updated to reflect `atom.length`. The `best_atom` struct ends up with a stale length, so subsequent use of `best_atom` either reads garbage bytes or ignores valid bytes, producing incorrect atom extraction results that cause the `test-atoms` suite to fail.\n\n**LOCAL FIX:** Restore the single deleted line inside the `if (quality > best_quality)` block, immediately after the copy loop:\n\n```c\n              for (i = 0; i < atom.length; i++)\n              {\n                best_atom.bytes[i] = atom.bytes[i];\n                best_atom.mask[i] = atom.mask[i];\n                best_atom_re_nodes[i] = recent_re_nodes[i + shift];\n              }\n\n+             best_atom.length = atom.length;   // ← restored line\n              best_quality = quality;\n```\n\n**GLOBAL FIX:** Replace the manual field-by-field copy of `atom` into `best_atom` with a single struct assignment (`best_atom = atom;`), which atomically copies all fields — bytes, mask, *and* length — in one operation. This eliminates the class of bug where a partial copy forgets one or more fields. Additionally, define a helper like `yr_atom_copy(YR_ATOM *dst, const YR_ATOM *src)` that encapsulates the full copy and is used everywhere atom structs need to be duplicated, so future additions of fields to `YR_ATOM` are automatically handled."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1298,"cache_read_input_tokens":24024,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1298},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0f350f05-a78a-4723-abb0-ecb1c5271ece","uuid":"da027fc7-8dc4-434b-b88e-caf8ad766947"}
